        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-08-28T16:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-08-28T16:16:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <head>5. Memorandum of Telephone Conversation Between the Secretary of State and the
                    President’s Special Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BMG1">Bundy</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d5fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>
                        Files: Lot 72 D 192, Telephone Conversations. Transcribed by Phyllis D.
                        Bernau.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1963-08-28T17:16:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1963—5:16 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">TELEPHONE CALL FROM MR <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">BUNDY</persName>
                </p>
                <p>B said the mtg at 6 is acquiring more importance because of a real possible split
                    between State and <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>-does not think it will be
                    the same without Sec because <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> is
                    so passionate and can’t speak for Dept as Sec can and Sec’s and Bob’s relation
                    is helpful. Sec will be there. B thinks Bob and <persName corresp="#p_TGMD1"
                        >Taylor</persName> think more than the record indicates that decisions taken
                    Sat were without adequate consultation between State and <gloss target="#t_DOD1"
                        >DOD</gloss>. B read from a message.<note n="2" xml:id="d5fn2">Apparent
                        reference to telegram <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 3368-63, <ref
                            target="frus1961-63v03#pg_675">vol. III, p. 675</ref>.</note> Pres
                    likely to start 6 p.m. mtg by talking with Sec, <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                        >McNamara</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_TGMD1">Taylor</persName> and B
                    as notetaker to get a slightly common front on this. B said <persName
                        corresp="#p_HRJ1">Hilsman</persName> has most of the stuff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
